modules.description: Provides functions to parse and transform OCaml syntax trees using extension points, including rewriting expressions and annotations. Operates on core OCaml types such as `expression`, `pattern`, and `type_expr`. Enables custom syntax handling in code generators and linters.

Provides functions to retrieve environment variables and process ppx extensions, including an expander for injecting environment values into code during parsing. Works with strings, location data, and ppx AST structures. Used to dynamically insert environment values into quoted expressions during preprocessing.
